#spec design feature

> Support for organising notes into subdirectories within eshp/.

## Problem

All notes currently live flat in eshp/. Slugs are derived from `path.stem` (filename only).
Three hard constraints make this flat-only:
  1. `sync()` uses `glob("*.eshp")` — not recursive
  2. `parse_eshp()` uses `path.stem` — no directory context
  3. Watchdog uses `recursive=False`

## Design: path-based slugs

Slugs become root-relative POSIX paths (no .eshp extension).

  eshp/store.eshp           → slug: store           (unchanged)
  eshp/concepts/auth.eshp   → slug: concepts/auth   (new)
  eshp/modules/api.eshp     → slug: modules/api     (new)

Always `/` separator (POSIX), even on Windows. DB stores them as plain TEXT — no schema change.
Top-level notes are fully backward compatible. Relationship refs must use full path-slug.

## Changes required

### eshp_parser.py
Add optional `root: Path = None` param to `parse_eshp()`.
When root is provided: slug = path.relative_to(root).as_posix().removesuffix(".eshp")
When root is None (default): slug = path.stem  ← backward compat for tests and `eshp new`

### eshp_store.py
sync(): change glob("*.eshp") → rglob("*.eshp")
sync(): pass root=self.root to parse_eshp()

### eshp_cli.py
EshpHandler._sync_file / _delete_file: path.stem → path.relative_to(store.root).as_posix().removesuffix(".eshp")
EshpHandler._sync_file: pass root=store.root to parse_eshp()
observer.schedule(): recursive=False → recursive=True  (both watch and serve)
eshp new: store.root / f"{slug}.eshp" → (store.root / slug).with_suffix(".eshp"); mkdir parents

## Out of scope
- Relative refs within files (e.g. -> ./sibling) — all refs are absolute from root
- Ambiguous short-slug resolution
- .eshpignore
- Rename/move tooling

## Test plan (TDD order)
1. test_parser.py: root param (no root→stem, with root→path-slug, top-level stays same)
2. test_store.py: sync finds subdir notes, path-slug upsert/get/delete, edges across dirs, search
3. CLI: EshpHandler + eshp new (subdirectory creation)

